348 // - ImMin/ImMax/ImClamp/ImLerp/ImSwap are used by widgets which support variety of types: signed/unsigned int/long long float/double
349 // (Exceptionally using templates here but we could also redefine them for those types)
350 template<typename T> static inline T ImMin(T lhs, T rhs) { return lhs < rhs ? lhs : rhs; }
351 template<typename T> static inline T ImMax(T lhs, T rhs) { return lhs >= rhs ? lhs : rhs; }
352 template<typename T> static inline T ImClamp(T v, T mn, T mx) { return (v < mn) ? mn : (v > mx) ? mx : v; }
353 template<typename T> static inline T ImLerp(T a, T b, float t) { return (T)(a + (b - a) * t); }
354 template<typename T> static inline void ImSwap(T& a, T& b) { T tmp = a; a = b; b = tmp; }
355 template<typename T> static inline T ImAddClampOverflow(T a, T b, T mn, T mx) { if (b < 0 && (a < mn - b)) return mn; if (b > 0 && (a > mx - b)) return mx; return a + b; }
356 template<typename T> static inline T ImSubClampOverflow(T a, T b, T mn, T mx) { if (b > 0 && (a < mn + b)) return mn; if (b < 0 && (a > mx + b)) return mx; return a - b; }

359 static inline ImVec2 ImMax(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x >= rhs.x ? lhs.x : rhs.x, lhs.y >= rhs.y ? lhs.y : rhs.y); }
360 static inline ImVec2 ImClamp(const ImVec2& v, const ImVec2& mn, ImVec2 mx) { return ImVec2((v.x < mn.x) ? mn.x : (v.x > mx.x) ? mx.x : v.x, (v.y < mn.y) ? mn.y : (v.y > mx.y) ? mx.y : v.y); }

362 static inline ImVec2 ImLerp(const ImVec2& a, const ImVec2& b, const ImVec2& t) { return ImVec2(a.x + (b.x - a.x) * t.x, a.y + (b.y - a.y) * t.y); }
363 static inline ImVec4 ImLerp(const ImVec4& a, const ImVec4& b, float t) { return ImVec4(a.x + (b.x - a.x) * t, a.y + (b.y - a.y) * t, a.z + (b.z - a.z) * t, a.w + (b.w - a.w) * t); }

367 static inline float ImInvLength(const ImVec2& lhs, float fail_value) { float d = (lhs.x * lhs.x) + (lhs.y * lhs.y); if (d > 0.0f) return 1.0f / ImSqrt(d); return fail_value; }
368 static inline float ImFloor(float f) { return (float)(int)(f); }

405 // Helper: ImRect (2D axis aligned bounding-box)
406 // NB: we can't rely on ImVec2 math operators being available here!
407 struct IMGUI_API ImRect
408 {
409  ImVec2 Min; // Upper-left
410  ImVec2 Max; // Lower-right
411 
412  ImRect() : Min(0.0f, 0.0f), Max(0.0f, 0.0f) {}
413  ImRect(const ImVec2& min, const ImVec2& max) : Min(min), Max(max) {}
414  ImRect(const ImVec4& v) : Min(v.x, v.y), Max(v.z, v.w) {}
415  ImRect(float x1, float y1, float x2, float y2) : Min(x1, y1), Max(x2, y2) {}
416 
417  ImVec2 GetCenter() const { return ImVec2((Min.x + Max.x) * 0.5f, (Min.y + Max.y) * 0.5f); }
418  ImVec2 GetSize() const { return ImVec2(Max.x - Min.x, Max.y - Min.y); }
419  float GetWidth() const { return Max.x - Min.x; }
420  float GetHeight() const { return Max.y - Min.y; }
421  ImVec2 GetTL() const { return Min; } // Top-left
422  ImVec2 GetTR() const { return ImVec2(Max.x, Min.y); } // Top-right
423  ImVec2 GetBL() const { return ImVec2(Min.x, Max.y); } // Bottom-left
424  ImVec2 GetBR() const { return Max; } // Bottom-right
425  bool Contains(const ImVec2& p) const { return p.x >= Min.x && p.y >= Min.y && p.x < Max.x && p.y < Max.y; }
426  bool Contains(const ImRect& r) const { return r.Min.x >= Min.x && r.Min.y >= Min.y && r.Max.x <= Max.x && r.Max.y <= Max.y; }
427  bool Overlaps(const ImRect& r) const { return r.Min.y < Max.y && r.Max.y > Min.y && r.Min.x < Max.x && r.Max.x > Min.x; }
428  void Add(const ImVec2& p) { if (Min.x > p.x) Min.x = p.x; if (Min.y > p.y) Min.y = p.y; if (Max.x < p.x) Max.x = p.x; if (Max.y < p.y) Max.y = p.y; }
429  void Add(const ImRect& r) { if (Min.x > r.Min.x) Min.x = r.Min.x; if (Min.y > r.Min.y) Min.y = r.Min.y; if (Max.x < r.Max.x) Max.x = r.Max.x; if (Max.y < r.Max.y) Max.y = r.Max.y; }
430  void Expand(const float amount) { Min.x -= amount; Min.y -= amount; Max.x += amount; Max.y += amount; }
431  void Expand(const ImVec2& amount) { Min.x -= amount.x; Min.y -= amount.y; Max.x += amount.x; Max.y += amount.y; }
432  void Translate(const ImVec2& d) { Min.x += d.x; Min.y += d.y; Max.x += d.x; Max.y += d.y; }
433  void TranslateX(float dx) { Min.x += dx; Max.x += dx; }
434  void TranslateY(float dy) { Min.y += dy; Max.y += dy; }
435  void ClipWith(const ImRect& r) { Min = ImMax(Min, r.Min); Max = ImMin(Max, r.Max); } // Simple version, may lead to an inverted rectangle, which is fine for Contains/Overlaps test but not for display.
436  void ClipWithFull(const ImRect& r) { Min = ImClamp(Min, r.Min, r.Max); Max = ImClamp(Max, r.Min, r.Max); } // Full version, ensure both points are fully clipped.
437  void Floor() { Min.x = IM_FLOOR(Min.x); Min.y = IM_FLOOR(Min.y); Max.x = IM_FLOOR(Max.x); Max.y = IM_FLOOR(Max.y); }
438  bool IsInverted() const { return Min.x > Max.x || Min.y > Max.y; }
439  ImVec4 ToVec4() const { return ImVec4(Min.x, Min.y, Max.x, Max.y); }
440 };

442 // Helper: ImBitArray
443 inline bool ImBitArrayTestBit(const ImU32* arr, int n) { ImU32 mask = (ImU32)1 << (n & 31); return (arr[n >> 5] & mask) != 0; }
444 inline void ImBitArrayClearBit(ImU32* arr, int n) { ImU32 mask = (ImU32)1 << (n & 31); arr[n >> 5] &= ~mask; }
445 inline void ImBitArraySetBit(ImU32* arr, int n) { ImU32 mask = (ImU32)1 << (n & 31); arr[n >> 5] |= mask; }
446 inline void ImBitArraySetBitRange(ImU32* arr, int n, int n2)
447 {
448  while (n <= n2)
449  {
450  int a_mod = (n & 31);
451  int b_mod = ((n2 >= n + 31) ? 31 : (n2 & 31)) + 1;
452  ImU32 mask = (ImU32)(((ImU64)1 << b_mod) - 1) & ~(ImU32)(((ImU64)1 << a_mod) - 1);
453  arr[n >> 5] |= mask;
454  n = (n + 32) & ~31;
455  }
456 }

458 // Helper: ImBitVector
459 // Store 1-bit per value.
460 struct IMGUI_API ImBitVector
461 {
462  ImVector<ImU32> Storage;
463  void Create(int sz) { Storage.resize((sz + 31) >> 5); memset(Storage.Data, 0, (size_t)Storage.Size * sizeof(Storage.Data[0])); }
464  void Clear() { Storage.clear(); }
465  bool TestBit(int n) const { IM_ASSERT(n < (Storage.Size << 5)); return ImBitArrayTestBit(Storage.Data, n); }
466  void SetBit(int n) { IM_ASSERT(n < (Storage.Size << 5)); ImBitArraySetBit(Storage.Data, n); }
467  void ClearBit(int n) { IM_ASSERT(n < (Storage.Size << 5)); ImBitArrayClearBit(Storage.Data, n); }
468 };

470 // Helper: ImPool<>
471 // Basic keyed storage for contiguous instances, slow/amortized insertion, O(1) indexable, O(Log N) queries by ID over a dense/hot buffer,
472 // Honor constructor/destructor. Add/remove invalidate all pointers. Indexes have the same lifetime as the associated object.
473 typedef int ImPoolIdx;
474 template<typename T>
475 struct IMGUI_API ImPool
476 {
477  ImVector<T> Buf; // Contiguous data
478  ImGuiStorage Map; // ID->Index
479  ImPoolIdx FreeIdx; // Next free idx to use
480 
481  ImPool() { FreeIdx = 0; }
482  ~ImPool() { Clear(); }
483  T* GetByKey(ImGuiID key) { int idx = Map.GetInt(key, -1); return (idx != -1) ? &Buf[idx] : NULL; }
484  T* GetByIndex(ImPoolIdx n) { return &Buf[n]; }
485  ImPoolIdx GetIndex(const T* p) const { IM_ASSERT(p >= Buf.Data && p < Buf.Data + Buf.Size); return (ImPoolIdx)(p - Buf.Data); }
486  T* GetOrAddByKey(ImGuiID key) { int* p_idx = Map.GetIntRef(key, -1); if (*p_idx != -1) return &Buf[*p_idx]; *p_idx = FreeIdx; return Add(); }
487  bool Contains(const T* p) const { return (p >= Buf.Data && p < Buf.Data + Buf.Size); }
488  void Clear() { for (int n = 0; n < Map.Data.Size; n++) { int idx = Map.Data[n].val_i; if (idx != -1) Buf[idx].~T(); } Map.Clear(); Buf.clear(); FreeIdx = 0; }
489  T* Add() { int idx = FreeIdx; if (idx == Buf.Size) { Buf.resize(Buf.Size + 1); FreeIdx++; } else { FreeIdx = *(int*)&Buf[idx]; } IM_PLACEMENT_NEW(&Buf[idx]) T(); return &Buf[idx]; }
490  void Remove(ImGuiID key, const T* p) { Remove(key, GetIndex(p)); }
491  void Remove(ImGuiID key, ImPoolIdx idx) { Buf[idx].~T(); *(int*)&Buf[idx] = FreeIdx; FreeIdx = idx; Map.SetInt(key, -1); }
492  void Reserve(int capacity) { Buf.reserve(capacity); Map.Data.reserve(capacity); }
493  int GetSize() const { return Buf.Size; }
494 };

496 // Helper: ImChunkStream<>
497 // Build and iterate a contiguous stream of variable-sized structures.
498 // This is used by Settings to store persistent data while reducing allocation count.
499 // We store the chunk size first, and align the final size on 4 bytes boundaries (this what the '(X + 3) & ~3' statement is for)
500 // The tedious/zealous amount of casting is to avoid -Wcast-align warnings.
501 template<typename T>
502 struct IMGUI_API ImChunkStream
503 {
504  ImVector<char> Buf;
505 
506  void clear() { Buf.clear(); }
507  bool empty() const { return Buf.Size == 0; }
508  int size() const { return Buf.Size; }
509  T* alloc_chunk(size_t sz) { size_t HDR_SZ = 4; sz = ((HDR_SZ + sz) + 3u) & ~3u; int off = Buf.Size; Buf.resize(off + (int)sz); ((int*)(void*)(Buf.Data + off))[0] = (int)sz; return (T*)(void*)(Buf.Data + off + (int)HDR_SZ); }
510  T* begin() { size_t HDR_SZ = 4; if (!Buf.Data) return NULL; return (T*)(void*)(Buf.Data + HDR_SZ); }
511  T* next_chunk(T* p) { size_t HDR_SZ = 4; IM_ASSERT(p >= begin() && p < end()); p = (T*)(void*)((char*)(void*)p + chunk_size(p)); if (p == (T*)(void*)((char*)end() + HDR_SZ)) return (T*)0; IM_ASSERT(p < end()); return p; }
512  int chunk_size(const T* p) { return ((const int*)p)[-1]; }
513  T* end() { return (T*)(void*)(Buf.Data + Buf.Size); }
514  int offset_from_ptr(const T* p) { IM_ASSERT(p >= begin() && p < end()); const ptrdiff_t off = (const char*)p - Buf.Data; return (int)off; }
515  T* ptr_from_offset(int off) { IM_ASSERT(off >= 4 && off < Buf.Size); return (T*)(void*)(Buf.Data + off); }
516 };
